exp ( − 1.288 ×  Ψ Pre ) ; exposed canopy, density = 0.164 × exp ( − 2.097 ×  Ψ Pre ) .

Thickness and predicted thickness also followed similar trends with height, light and Ψ Pre to those observed for both LMA and density (Figure 5 ). The interaction terms height × canopy type and Ψ Pre  × canopy type were significant, but not the interaction term ln(light) × canopy type (Table 3 ). Intercepts for all relationships were significantly different between canopy types ( P  < 0.05). (ln)Light explained more variation in predicted leaf thickness than did Ψ Pre (Table 4 ). Partial R 2 values for adding (ln)light (0.15–0.44) to the full model for predicting (ln)thickness were greater compared with adding Ψ Pre (0.04, Table 4 ).
